==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Frisk
<hw>Frisk</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[OF. <ets>frieque</ets>,
cf. OHG. <ets>frise</ets> lively, brisk, fresh, Dan. & Sw.
<ets>frisk</ets>, Icel. <ets>friskr</ets>. See <er>Fresh</er>,
<pos>a.</pos>]</ety> <def>Lively; brisk; frolicsome; frisky.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Bp. Hall.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Frisk</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Frisk
<hw>Frisk</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>A frolic; a fit of wanton gayety; a
gambol: a little playful skip or leap.</def>
<rj><au>Johnson.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Frisk</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Frisk
<hw>Frisk</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos>
<conjf>Frisked</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Frisking</conjf>.]</vmorph> <def>To leap, skip, dance, or gambol,
in fronc and gayety.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The <qex>frisking</qex> satyrs on the summits danced.</q>
<rj><qau>Addison.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>frisk</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 4 ====
HEADWORD: frisk
<hw>frisk</hw> <pr>(fr⟦icr⟧sk)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To search (a
person) for concealed weapons or other objects, by patting the clothing
to detect objects underneath; <as>as, the police pulled the car over and
<ex>frisked</ex> the occupants</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> frisk.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Friskal</ent>⟦br⟧
